  <scopecontent id="aspace_720ac969e2ecf83017cdf327626231c8">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Papers of the Snow family (1782-1865) of Truro, Massachusetts, include letters, land contracts, and a poem. Papers of the Gross family (1861-1884) include letters pertaining to the Civil War, a water cure, and life in Washington and Oregon.</p>  </scopecontent>
